{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Create national \"Low Demand School Hubs\" for students with EBSA, ODD, and PDA",
        "additional_details": "Current \"inclusion bases\" within mainstream schools are often insufficient\u2014acting like a band-aid on a broken leg. Students with these profiles require an environment built on autonomy, collaborative communication, and sensory regulation, rather than the high-pressure, rigid structures of traditional education.",
        "background": "The Government should provide funding and a national framework for \"Low-Demand School Hubs\" specifically designed for students with Emotional Based School Avoidance (EBSA), Oppositional Defiant Disorder (ODD), and Pathological Demand Avoidance (PDA).",
